WEBVTT

00:01.040 --> 00:02.997
Previously on
"Life Sentence"...

00:03.040 --> 00:05.782
Wes: And I bumped into you.
Everything changed.

00:05.840 --> 00:08.582
I was supposed to marry Pippa.
Five days before I met you.

00:08.630 --> 00:10.587
You're not dying.
I'm cured.

00:10.630 --> 00:12.371
Stella: My cancer was gone

00:12.430 --> 00:14.171
and the eight years my family
spent taking care of me

00:14.220 --> 00:15.927
had kind of ruined
their lives.

00:15.970 --> 00:17.677
You're under arrest.

00:18.680 --> 00:20.091
You really did
get off easy.

00:20.140 --> 00:21.801
Easy?!

00:21.850 --> 00:24.478
I got a week in jail,
150 hours of community service,

00:24.520 --> 00:27.353
and I have to wear
a tracking anklet with a curfew.

00:27.400 --> 00:29.858
You have to stop
offering me rides

00:29.900 --> 00:31.811
and...amazing advice

00:31.860 --> 00:33.146
and -- and making me feel like

00:33.200 --> 00:34.736
you're the only person
on Earth

00:34.780 --> 00:36.817
who really gets me.

00:37.990 --> 00:39.697
Calluses are sexy.

00:39.740 --> 00:41.401
They're a sign of somebody
who's willing to do the work.

00:41.450 --> 00:43.748
You know I'm not here
'cause I wanna be, right?

00:43.790 --> 00:45.167
I'm aware.

00:45.210 --> 00:46.700
I got a job interview
in San Francisco.

00:46.750 --> 00:48.036
Pippa set it up.
Pippa?

00:48.090 --> 00:49.160
Yeah.

00:49.210 --> 00:50.541
She recommended me
for it.

00:50.590 --> 00:52.126
How am I supposed
to feel about this?

00:52.170 --> 00:53.376
I trusted you.

00:53.420 --> 00:55.468
_ Now
it's your turn to trust me.

00:55.510 --> 01:00.175
[ Layup's "Growing Pains"
plays ]

01:00.220 --> 01:02.632
Since Wes left
for San Francisco,

01:02.680 --> 01:04.262
I'd barely slept.

01:04.310 --> 01:06.392
Thank God he was coming home
this morning.

01:06.440 --> 01:09.262
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh

01:09.320 --> 01:11.357
I, oh, I

01:11.400 --> 01:14.028
I got these growing pains

01:14.070 --> 01:18.985
When the storm wind blows,
I'm the weather vane

01:19.030 --> 01:20.691
I, oh, I

01:20.740 --> 01:23.448
I'm made from what remains

01:23.500 --> 01:28.165
Thick skin, knowing
it's just growing pains

01:31.880 --> 01:34.463
Only problem?
Wes was late.

01:34.510 --> 01:36.831
So I was late for work.

01:44.770 --> 01:46.226
Hi.

01:46.270 --> 01:48.056
Hi.

01:50.400 --> 01:52.937
Sorry.
The plane was delayed.

01:52.980 --> 01:55.813
San Francisco
has a lot of fog.

01:55.860 --> 01:57.350
Reminded me of London.

01:57.400 --> 01:59.152
I-I wanna
to hear everything.

01:59.200 --> 02:00.941
Like did you see Pippa?

02:00.990 --> 02:02.116
Oh, you've got to work,
right?

02:02.160 --> 02:03.480
I can just fill you in
later.

02:03.540 --> 02:04.746
Or you could just give me
the highlights.

02:04.790 --> 02:06.155
Like did you see Pippa?

02:06.210 --> 02:08.918
Actually, uh,
we probably should talk now.

02:08.960 --> 02:10.416
Oh, God.
You saw Pippa.

02:10.460 --> 02:13.703
I-I did not see Pippa.

02:13.750 --> 02:15.252
Oh, good.

02:15.300 --> 02:17.291
Though I-I wouldn't blame you
if you did.

02:17.340 --> 02:18.501
Talk to her, I mean.

02:18.550 --> 02:20.757
She did get you
the interview.

02:20.800 --> 02:22.290
I'm -- I'm sorry.

02:22.350 --> 02:24.591
I-I think I'm just feeling
really guilty about Seattle.

02:24.640 --> 02:26.631
Should we sit? Do you want
some tea? I made some tea.

02:26.680 --> 02:27.886
They offered me the job,
Stell.

02:30.230 --> 02:31.516
Oh.

02:31.560 --> 02:33.608
It's a really great job.

02:33.650 --> 02:36.312
I mean, I wouldn't
just be moving money around.

02:36.360 --> 02:39.273
I would actually be helping
real companies

02:39.320 --> 02:42.119
do real things to make
the world a better place.

02:42.160 --> 02:43.946
Wow.

02:43.990 --> 02:48.655
That sounds really...real.

02:48.710 --> 02:50.997
It is.

02:51.040 --> 02:53.202
And they need an answer
tomorrow.

02:53.250 --> 02:59.292
Wes, I-I don't know if I can
move to San Francisco right now.

02:59.340 --> 03:00.922
But we don't have to move.

03:00.970 --> 03:02.506
That's why it's perfect.

03:02.550 --> 03:04.712
Eventually,
I could work from here.

03:04.760 --> 03:06.421
But...currently?

03:06.470 --> 03:09.633
Well, you know,
for the first couple years,

03:09.690 --> 03:11.340
I'd probably have
to be there a lot.

03:11.400 --> 03:13.937
But, still,
I could come back on weekends.

03:13.980 --> 03:16.608
And you could come
when you can.

03:16.650 --> 03:18.311
The company said
that they'll pay for travel,

03:18.360 --> 03:20.988
and we'd rack up
frequent flyer miles,

03:21.030 --> 03:24.193
and we'd have enough
for a trip to Paris so soon.

03:26.490 --> 03:27.696
What do you think?

03:27.750 --> 03:30.321
I think...

03:31.830 --> 03:34.162
...you deserve it.

03:34.210 --> 03:35.166
Let's do it.

03:35.210 --> 03:36.166
Wait. Really?

03:36.210 --> 03:38.087
Absolutely. Yeah.

03:44.930 --> 03:46.341
Hey! You're late!

03:46.390 --> 03:48.461
I know. I'm so sorry.
Crazy morning.

03:48.520 --> 03:51.512
Wes' plane was delayed
and...

03:52.900 --> 03:54.095
You're gone.

03:54.150 --> 03:55.606
So, what do you need?

03:55.650 --> 03:57.311
Register help or --

03:57.360 --> 03:59.101
I need you to turn in
your end-of-the-month time card

03:59.150 --> 04:00.811
so I can pay you.
What do you mean?

04:00.860 --> 04:02.817
You know the words
I just said out loud?

04:02.860 --> 04:05.818
I mean those. Yeah, but the end
of the month isn't for another week.

04:05.870 --> 04:08.328
Yeah, well, time flies
when you're constantly tardy.

04:08.370 --> 04:10.532
Check the calendar.
-Wait.

04:10.580 --> 04:11.820
If it's the end of the month,

04:11.870 --> 04:14.168
I didn't pay any of my bills
and...

04:17.380 --> 04:19.291
Stella: I was late
for something else, too.

04:19.339 --> 04:20.875
Hey.

04:20.920 --> 04:23.548
I am so sorry for being late
today, but I have to go.

04:23.590 --> 04:25.046
But I-I'll be right back.

04:25.090 --> 04:28.469
You are the worst person
who's ever worked here!

04:29.810 --> 04:33.303
You're a close second.

04:33.350 --> 04:35.682
The funny thing
about a pregnancy test is,

04:35.730 --> 04:39.064
being pregnant
is always a positive...

04:39.110 --> 04:40.726
even though
the test has no idea

04:40.780 --> 04:42.236
how you'll actually feel
about it.

04:48.660 --> 04:51.652
Don't worry about a thing

04:51.700 --> 04:55.580
You'll learn to live again

04:55.620 --> 04:57.247
You're gonna learn
to live again

04:57.290 --> 05:02.080
Oh, oh, oh

05:05.430 --> 05:07.330
Oh. Hey.

05:07.390 --> 05:08.926
Do you mind
if I order from my sister?

05:08.970 --> 05:10.176
She knows
how I like my coffee.

05:10.220 --> 05:11.676
How does
she like her coffee?

05:11.720 --> 05:13.017
Free.

05:13.060 --> 05:14.516
Thanks!

05:14.560 --> 05:16.801
So, how was Wes' interview?

05:16.850 --> 05:18.852
Did he see Pippa?
How are you feeling?

05:18.900 --> 05:21.642
He got the job.
He did not see Pippa.

05:21.690 --> 05:23.237
And I'm feeling pregnant.

05:23.280 --> 05:25.897
What?

05:25.950 --> 05:27.907
Oh, my God!
You're pregnant?!

05:27.950 --> 05:29.577
Lizzie, you are at a 10.

05:29.620 --> 05:32.032
I'm gonna need you at a 2.

05:32.080 --> 05:33.570
How do you feel?

05:33.620 --> 05:36.328
Um...overwhelmed.

05:36.370 --> 05:37.952
Terrified.

05:38.000 --> 05:39.877
On a scale of 1 to,
"How can I do this right now?"

05:39.920 --> 05:42.127
I am solidly at, "How can
I do this right now?"

05:42.170 --> 05:43.456
I just got my life back,

05:43.510 --> 05:45.547
and Wes is taking this job
out of town,

05:45.590 --> 05:47.467
and all this stuff
with Dr. Grant and Pippa,

05:47.510 --> 05:49.421
we're not
exactly crushing it.

05:49.470 --> 05:50.881
And I know that
there is never a good time

05:50.930 --> 05:52.420
to have an "oops" baby,
but if there was,

05:52.470 --> 05:53.926
this is definitely not it.

05:53.970 --> 05:55.597
Okay.

05:56.690 --> 05:58.761
But I'm also
really excited.

06:00.020 --> 06:01.567
Lizzie, I really want
to be a mom,

06:01.610 --> 06:04.102
and I never thought
that I'd get the chance to.

06:04.150 --> 06:05.982
And Wes wants kids,
and we're married,

06:06.030 --> 06:07.816
so that might be fate,
you know?

06:07.860 --> 06:09.612
Then again, I can't even
take care of a cactus,

06:09.660 --> 06:11.150
and that requires
zero effort,

06:11.200 --> 06:12.577
so I am definitely gonna
forget to water the baby.

06:12.620 --> 06:13.826
Stella.

06:13.870 --> 06:14.940
Breathe.

06:16.500 --> 06:17.570
Come here.

06:19.460 --> 06:21.280
Congratulations.

06:21.340 --> 06:23.627
You're gonna be
a rock-star mom.

06:25.050 --> 06:27.712
I have repeatedly screwed up
taking care of your children.

06:27.760 --> 06:30.047
They survived,
and they adore you.

06:30.090 --> 06:31.751
You're gonna be amazing
at this.

06:31.800 --> 06:33.632
You really think so?

06:33.680 --> 06:35.091
I really do.

06:36.770 --> 06:38.556
Okay.
Okay.

06:38.600 --> 06:40.011
Well, I am choosing
to believe you

06:40.060 --> 06:41.858
because,
out of everyone I know,

06:41.900 --> 06:44.221
you are the one person who is
always 100% straight with me.

06:44.270 --> 06:45.772
Mm. Oh, but can
you not tell anyone?

06:45.820 --> 06:47.527
I'm still figuring out
how to tell Wes,

06:47.570 --> 06:49.732
and I-I'm so nervous.

06:49.780 --> 06:51.487
He's gonna be thrilled.

06:51.530 --> 06:54.989
Hey, you got this, sis.

06:55.040 --> 06:56.439
Oh, and before I go,

06:56.500 --> 06:58.116
Aiden wanted me to get
two of his favorite coffees.

06:58.160 --> 06:59.912
I assume, by "favorite,”
you mean "free."

06:59.960 --> 07:02.201
Totally.

07:02.250 --> 07:04.958
The dog park is full
of people looking to get laid.

07:05.000 --> 07:07.583
Basically, it's like going
to a bar during the daytime

07:07.630 --> 07:10.839
with no alcohol and a wingman
who pees on your foot.

07:10.880 --> 07:12.291
I've been that wingman.

07:13.640 --> 07:15.551
Hey, um, thanks again
for the coffee.

07:15.600 --> 07:16.635
What do I owe you?

07:16.680 --> 07:18.227
Nah, it's cool.

07:18.270 --> 07:20.307
I don't mind throwing money
around for the big boss.

07:20.350 --> 07:22.978
Aw, you were doing so well
before you said the word "big."

07:23.020 --> 07:24.431
But big is a good thing.

07:24.480 --> 07:25.436
Just quit while you're ahead.

07:25.480 --> 07:26.686
Am I ahead?

07:26.730 --> 07:29.734
It's unclear.

07:29.780 --> 07:31.817
Anyway...time to work.

07:34.780 --> 07:37.659
What do you mean?
I got here like an hour early.

07:37.700 --> 07:39.077
That's how long
we've been talking.

07:39.120 --> 07:40.997
We've been talking
for an hour?

07:41.040 --> 07:43.748
Whoa, I've never talked
to a chick for an hour before.

07:43.790 --> 07:45.201
I mean a girl.

07:45.250 --> 07:46.331
Lady?

07:46.380 --> 07:48.291
I prefer "broad."”
Really?

07:48.340 --> 07:50.251
Absolutely not.

07:54.930 --> 07:57.752
Hey, do you mind if I put the
floor cleaner on a high shelf?

07:57.810 --> 08:00.268
We don't want toxic chemicals
at the kids' snacking height.

08:00.310 --> 08:02.688
I truly do not care
where you put anything.

08:02.730 --> 08:05.051
Diego, do you know
where Fiona's pink elephant is?

08:05.110 --> 08:07.147
She wants to take it to school,
and I can't seem to --

08:07.190 --> 08:08.897
Does no one see
that I'm trying to work here?

08:08.940 --> 08:10.351
Oh, excuse us.

08:10.400 --> 08:12.107
We were just trying to take care
of your children.

08:12.150 --> 08:14.027
I'm sorry.

08:14.070 --> 08:17.028
Look, I do appreciate that.
I'm just trying to focus.

08:17.080 --> 08:18.946
There's this new territory
up for grabs at work,

08:18.990 --> 08:20.287
and I really want it.

08:20.330 --> 08:21.866
I thought you were close
with your boss.

08:21.910 --> 08:24.880
Yeah, he transferred, and
my new boss is not yet a fan.

08:24.920 --> 08:27.287
So I still got
to win her over.

08:27.340 --> 08:29.411
You should have Ida
make her brunch.

08:29.460 --> 08:30.871
That is a great idea.

08:30.920 --> 08:33.719
We can kill her
with kindness and carbs.

08:33.760 --> 08:34.830
You think that'll work?

08:34.890 --> 08:36.961
How do you think
I got tenure?

08:37.010 --> 08:38.307
Boom!

08:38.350 --> 08:40.557
Please don't ever
do that again.

08:42.480 --> 08:45.017
I was waiting
for the perfect moment

08:45.060 --> 08:47.188
to tell Wes about the baby.

08:47.230 --> 08:49.608
But this wasn't it.

08:49.650 --> 08:52.893
Why are
we driving through a cemetery?

08:52.950 --> 08:55.191
Because, this way,
we avoid Market Street,

08:55.240 --> 08:58.028
which cuts off two blocks
and a traffic light.

08:58.080 --> 08:59.821
Got it.

08:59.870 --> 09:01.747
So...

09:03.580 --> 09:05.491
...have you said yes
to the job yet?

09:05.540 --> 09:08.248
Are they excited?
Yeah, I can't wait to start.

09:08.290 --> 09:09.997
It's like
a whole new adventure.

09:10.050 --> 09:11.085
I'm pregnant.
What?!

09:28.020 --> 09:30.011
-Yeah, I'm fine.

09:30.070 --> 09:31.356
I just...

09:31.400 --> 09:34.188
feel bad
for Mr. Klapholz.

09:34.240 --> 09:36.026
How did this happen?
It doesn't say.

09:36.070 --> 09:38.368
It just says he was a husband,
father, and grandfather.

09:38.410 --> 09:39.946
No, I mean us.

09:39.990 --> 09:42.118
We've been careful.

09:42.160 --> 09:44.492
Yeah, we have.

09:44.540 --> 09:46.451
But...not always.

09:46.500 --> 09:48.707
And apparently not enough.

09:51.750 --> 09:53.832
How do you feel
about all this?

09:53.880 --> 09:57.839
I'm overjoyed, actually.

09:57.880 --> 09:59.336
You are?

09:59.390 --> 10:00.789
Yeah.

10:00.850 --> 10:03.342
I mean, this is
what we've wanted, right?

10:04.520 --> 10:06.682
I'm gonna be a dad.

10:06.730 --> 10:08.550
I'm gonna be a dad!

10:10.610 --> 10:11.975
You hear that,
Mr. Klapholz?!

10:12.020 --> 10:13.897
I'm gonna be a dad!

10:13.940 --> 10:15.681
And you're gonna be a mom.

10:15.740 --> 10:18.607
I'm so glad you understand
how parenthood works.

10:18.660 --> 10:21.152
We're gonna be parents!

10:22.740 --> 10:25.038
We were so happy
we were literally dancing

10:25.080 --> 10:26.070
on someone's grave.

10:27.410 --> 10:30.869
My grandfather
was a terrible person.

10:32.460 --> 10:34.371
Sorry for your loss.
sorry.

10:34.420 --> 10:37.162
Just like that, all the crap
with Dr. Grant and Pippa

10:37.220 --> 10:39.086
didn't matter anymore.

10:39.130 --> 10:40.586
It was just us now.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.460
Well, us and a baby.

11:00.410 --> 11:01.650
Yes?

11:01.700 --> 11:04.112
Question --

11:04.160 --> 11:06.071
Do you know how many women
I've slept with?

11:07.500 --> 11:08.615
Me neither.

11:08.660 --> 11:10.412
But every single one of them,

11:10.460 --> 11:12.371
I could tell you exactly
what they look like naked.

11:12.420 --> 11:13.740
Every detail.

11:13.790 --> 11:15.292
Grab me a piece of paper
and a number 2 pencil,

11:15.340 --> 11:17.661
and I can accurately sketch
them nude from memory.

11:17.710 --> 11:19.462
We all have gifts.

11:19.510 --> 11:21.046
But I couldn't tell you
if any one of them

11:21.090 --> 11:23.548
had jobs, hobbies,
feelings...

11:23.600 --> 11:25.557
Aiden, where are
you going with this?

11:25.600 --> 11:28.422
Kayla's different.
I actually like talking to her.

11:28.480 --> 11:30.767
I like listening to her.

11:30.810 --> 11:34.053
So, um,
what is the problem?

11:34.110 --> 11:35.896
Since I can't go out at night
or drink,

11:35.940 --> 11:37.567
my moves are out the window.

11:37.610 --> 11:40.318
Well, what do you know
about this girl?

11:40.360 --> 11:41.907
What does she like?
Uh...

11:41.950 --> 11:44.362
she has a ridiculously large
LEGO pirate-ship collection,

11:44.410 --> 11:45.946
which is totally weird,
but it's kind of cool

11:45.990 --> 11:47.537
that she'd admit that.

11:47.580 --> 11:50.117
Well, you need to find
something you both like...

11:50.160 --> 11:51.491
a common interest.

11:59.210 --> 12:01.372
Hey.
Kayla has a dog.

12:01.430 --> 12:03.171
You're not stealing
our neighbor's dog.

12:03.220 --> 12:05.757
I would never do that.

12:05.800 --> 12:07.677
But I would borrow it.

12:09.930 --> 12:11.728
Gina, thanks again
for coming over.

12:11.770 --> 12:13.511
Happy to.

12:13.560 --> 12:16.564
New in town, so my weekends
are pretty open at the moment.

12:16.610 --> 12:20.069
-I'd love a mimosa,

12:20.110 --> 12:21.987
<i>minus the 0.].</i>

12:22.030 --> 12:23.941
Ah, I like the way you think.
Make that two.

12:23.990 --> 12:25.731
I like the way you drink.

12:25.780 --> 12:27.657
Now, Gina, this is
my new experiment --

12:27.700 --> 12:29.407
gluten-free crusts.

12:29.450 --> 12:30.690
Try and see how...

12:30.750 --> 12:32.366
You know what?
Close your eyes.

12:32.410 --> 12:34.367
Oh, uh, Mom,

12:34.420 --> 12:36.991
I-I-I-I don't think
Gina wants to...

12:37.040 --> 12:39.372
Okay, fine.
Don't close your eyes.

12:39.420 --> 12:40.910
Because they are beautiful.

12:40.960 --> 12:42.758
-Oh, Lord.
-Thank you, Ida.

12:42.800 --> 12:44.541
You're the second person
that told me that this week.

12:44.590 --> 12:46.752
I think it's because
I started wearing contacts.

12:46.800 --> 12:49.508
Oh, I bet you looked adorable
in glasses, too.

12:49.560 --> 12:51.210
Nah. I didn't have
the face for it.

12:51.270 --> 12:52.635
Yeah, you do, girl.

12:52.680 --> 12:54.262
Oh, thanks, girl.

12:54.310 --> 12:56.187
Yeah, excuse me one moment.

12:56.230 --> 12:57.857
Diego,
where's the ladies' room?

12:57.900 --> 13:00.892
It is, uh, down the hall
and to the right.

13:00.940 --> 13:02.567
Okay.
Hey, while you're in there,

13:02.610 --> 13:04.237
look at your cheekbones
in the mirror.

13:04.280 --> 13:06.157
I'm telling you -- stunning.

13:06.200 --> 13:07.156
Oh.

13:08.490 --> 13:09.980
What the hell was that?

13:10.040 --> 13:11.906
The first step
to Diego's promotion.

13:11.950 --> 13:14.920
You are locked in, my friend,
because that lady digs me.

13:14.960 --> 13:17.281
Really? I mean, you --
you really think so?

13:17.330 --> 13:19.378
Yep.
My gay-dar is going off.

13:19.420 --> 13:20.740
Or is it my bi

13:20.800 --> 13:22.416
Either way,
that new territory

13:22.460 --> 13:24.121
is as good as yours,
D-dawg.

13:24.170 --> 13:26.252
For the record, I didn't sign
off on that nickname. No.

13:26.300 --> 13:28.007
You're welcome.

13:28.050 --> 13:30.428
Okay, what about Petunia?

13:30.470 --> 13:31.676
No.

13:31.720 --> 13:33.927
That sounds like
a grandma name.

13:33.980 --> 13:35.095
Arabella?

